$
$ Database for Ag-Te from J. Korb 2004 (included in LB Vol. 5)
$
$ J. Korb, unpublished, GTT, 2004.
$
$ Dataset created 2013.05.30 by Bengt Hallstedt.
$ 2020.12.20: Modified for use with GES6.
$
$ Unary Te has changed considerably since 91Din. 04Kor and lb5-v2 uses the
$ original 91Din Te unary data and not the current 95Dav data. Using the
$ current Te unary data results in changes in invariant equilibria in the
$ Te-rich part of the system. The eutectic is at 534.6 K instead of 553.1 K.
$
$ AgTe (prototype AgTe, oP32, Pnma, empressite) is considered metastable.
$
$ The Ag5Te3 phase (in particular) has mighty strange temperature intervals;
$ a series of slightly different, constant heat capacities.
$
$ The original, very low, maximum temperatures for the Gibbs energy
$ expressions have been removed.
$
$ ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 TEMP-LIM 298.15 6000.00 !
$
$ELEMENT NAME  REF. STATE               ATOMIC MASS H298-H0    S298    !
$
 ELEMENT VA   VACUUM                      0.0          0.0      0.0    ! 
 ELEMENT AG   FCC_A1                    107.8682    5745.      42.55   ! 
 ELEMENT TE   HEXAGONAL_A8              127.60      6080.      49.221  ! 
$ ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ Species
$
 SPECIE  AG2                                AG2 !
 SPECIE  AG2TE                              AG2TE1 !
 SPECIE  AGTE                               AG1TE1 !
 SPECIE  TE2                                TE2 !
 SPECIE  TE3                                TE3 !
 SPECIE  TE4                                TE4 !
 SPECIE  TE5                                TE5 !
 SPECIE  TE6                                TE6 !
 SPECIE  TE7                                TE7 !
$ ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ Phase definitions
$
 PHASE LIQUID:L % 1 1 !
 CONST LIQUID:L : AG AG2TE TE : !
$
$ Fcc (cF4, Fm-3m) and MeX (cF8, Fm-3m)
$
 PHASE FCC_A1 %A 2 1 1 !
 CONST FCC_A1 : AG : VA : !
$
$ Bcc (cI2, Im-3m)
$
 PHASE BCC_A2 %B 2 1 3 !
 CONST BCC_A2 : AG : VA : !
$
$ Hcp (hP2, P6_3/mmc) and Me2X (NiAs-type, hP4, P6_3/mmc, B8_1)
$
 PHASE HCP_A3 %A 2 1 0.5 !
 CONST HCP_A3 : AG : VA : !
$
$ Prototype gamma-Se (hP3, P3_121)
$ The phase is named HEXAGONAL_A8 in the SGTE unary database and
$ TRIGONAL_A8 in LB.
$
 PHASE HEXAGONAL_A8 % 1 1 !
 CONST HEXAGONAL_A8 : TE : !
$
$ Prototype Ag2Te (mP12, P2_1/c), alpha-Ag2Te
$ Prototype Cu2Se-beta (cF44, Fm-3m), beta-Ag2Te
$ Prototype Ag2S (cI20, Im-3m), gamma-Ag2Te
$
 PHASE AG2TE % 2 2 1 !
 CONST AG2TE : AG : TE : !
$
$ Unknown structure
$
 PHASE AG19TE10 % 2 1.9 1 !
 CONST AG19TE10 : AG : TE : !
$
$ Prototype Ag5Te3 (hP155, P-62m), alpha-Ag5Te3
$ The structure of beta-Ag5Te3 is unknown
$
 PHASE AG5TE3 % 2 1.64 1 !
 CONST AG5TE3 : AG : TE : !
$
 PHASE GAS:G % 1 1 !
 CONST GAS:G : AG AG2 AG2TE AGTE TE TE2 TE3 TE4 TE5 TE6 TE7 : !
$ ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ Defaults
$
 DEFINE-SYSTEM-DEFAULT ELEMENT 2 !
 DEFAULT-COM DEFINE_SYSTEM_ELEMENT VA !
 TYPE-DEF % SEQ * !
 TYPE-DEF A GES AMEND_PHASE_DESCRIPTION @ MAGNETIC -3 0.28 !
 TYPE-DEF B GES AMEND_PHASE_DESCRIPTION @ MAGNETIC -1 0.4 !
 FUNCTION ZERO      298.15  0;                                         6000 N !
 FUNCTION UN_ASS    298.15  0;                                         6000 N !
 FUNCTION R         298.15  +8.31451;                                  6000 N !
$ ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ Element data
$ ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ Ag
$
$ CUB_A13 added in unary 3.0
$ CUB_A13 revised in unary 4.1
$ BCT_A5 added in unary 4.1
$
 PAR  G(FCC_A1,AG:VA),,                 +GHSERAG;                3000 N 91Din !
 PAR  G(HCP_A3,AG:VA),,                 +GHSERAG+300+0.3*T;      3000 N 91Din !
 PAR  G(BCC_A2,AG:VA),,                 +GHSERAG+3400-1.05*T;    3000 N 91Din !
$PAR  G(CUB_A13,AG:VA),,                +GHSERAG+3400-1.05*T;    3000 N 95Lim !
$PAR  G(CUB_A13,AG:VA),,                +GHSERAG
$            +3765.6-1.8826*T;                                   3000 N 96SGUN !
$PAR  G(BCT_A5,AG:VA),,                 +GHSERAG+4184.1;         3000 N 96Oh !
 PAR  G(LIQUID,AG),,                    +GLIQAG;                 3000 N 91Din !
$
 PAR  G(GAS,AG),,                       +FAG+RTLNP;,,                 N 94SGT !
 PAR  G(GAS,AG2),,                      +FAG2+RTLNP;,,                N 94SGT !
$
 FUNCTION GHSERAG   298.15  -7209.512+118.202013*T-23.8463314*T*LN(T)
       -0.001790585*T**2-3.98587E-07*T**3-12011*T**(-1);
      1234.93  Y  -15095.252+190.266404*T-33.472*T*LN(T)+1.411773E+29*T**(-9);
      3000.00  N !
 FUNCTION GLIQAG    298.15  +11025.076-8.89102*T+GHSERAG-1.033905E-20*T**7;
      1234.93  Y  -3587.111+180.964656*T-33.472*T*LN(T);
      3000.00  N !
$ Ag (g) :
